Windows 11 (2021+)

Overview:

Latest Microsoft desktop OS, successor to Windows 10.

Focuses on modern UI, productivity, and gaming.

Designed for both home and business users.

Feature updates: 21H2, 22H2, 25H2 (latest).

Editions:

Home – standard for personal PCs.

Pro – adds business tools, encryption, domain join.

Enterprise – for large organizations, advanced security and management.

Education – for schools/universities.

System Requirements:

64-bit CPU, 2+ cores, 1 GHz+ clock.

4 GB+ RAM (8 GB+ recommended).

64 GB+ storage.

UEFI firmware with Secure Boot & TPM 2.0.

DirectX 12 compatible GPU.

High-DPI display recommended.

Key Features:

Start Menu & Taskbar: Centered, simplified, widgets support.

Snap Layouts & Virtual Desktops: Better multitasking.

Microsoft Store: Apps, games, media, and Android apps (via Amazon Appstore).

Gaming: DirectStorage, Auto HDR, Xbox Game Pass integration.

Security: Windows Hello (face/fingerprint login), BitLocker, Defender Antivirus.

Teams Integration: Chat & video calls built-in.

Widgets: Weather, calendar, news, and custom feeds.

Touch & Pen Support: Optimized for tablets and hybrid devices.

Compatibility: Runs most Windows 10 apps and software.

Updates: Regular feature and security updates to keep system secure.

Deployment & Installation:

ISO files available for all editions and languages.

Can install fresh, upgrade from Windows 10, or run in virtual machines.

Multiple editions included in ISO; edition choice depends on product key.

Performance & UX:

Faster boot and system responsiveness on modern hardware.

Modern animations, rounded corners, and new sounds/UI elements.

Better multitasking, improved touch and pen input, optimized for hybrid devices.

Notes:

Strict hardware requirements compared to Windows 10.

Focused on future-proofing Windows ecosystem and cloud integration.
